    <stitle>HOOD, GRILLE, FENDERS AND BUMPER - 8600 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - GRILLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>GRILLE</title>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille - Removal</title>
            <figure id="f0900832" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900832.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="312px"
                         scalefitheight="312px"/>
                <caption>Figure 32. Grille And Shroud Removal</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE SHROUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GRILLE INSERT</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <para>The grille is a two piece chromed injection molded assembly (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f0900832">Figure 32</hotlnk>), designed with an aerodynamic styling to enhance the
                overall appearance of the 8600 series truck chassis.
            </para>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Locate the four lower grille and shroud mounting screws on the grille assembly (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f0900833">Figure 33, Item 3</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the screws.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To remove the grille assembly, lift the grille and shroud assembly out.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Grille - Install</title>
            <para>Prior to installing the grille and shroud assembly, inspect the mounting tabs on the inner upper
                surface of the shroud. Insure that all tabs are functional and in place.
            </para>
            <figure id="f0900833" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic filename="../figg09/G0900833.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="352px"
                         scalefitheight="352px"/>
                <caption>Figure 33. Grille Installation</caption>
                <calloutgroup>
                    <callout1>1. GRILLE SHROUD</callout1>
                    <callout1>2. GRILLE MOUNTING HOLES</callout1>
                    <callout1>3. GRILLE MOUNTING TAB INSERT SLOTS</callout1>
                    <callout1>4. HOOD</callout1>
                    <callout1>5. GRILLE INSERT</callout1>
                    <callout1>6. GRILLE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                </calloutgroup>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Align the four (4) upper mounting holes.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insert the upper grille/shroud mounting bolts in the grille mounting holes. Hand tighten
                    only.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Insure the alignment of the lower bolt mounting holes, insert the four mounting screws
                    in the assembly and tighten.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Tighten to 3 to 3.3 lbf-ft (4 to 4.5 Nm).</para>
            </step1>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Do not overtighten the mounting screws.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
